
[1]vocative

   VOC'ATIVE, a. [L. vocativus.] Relating to calling; as the vocative case
   in grammar.

   VOC'ATIVE, n. In grammar, the fifth case or state of nouns in the Latin
   language; or the case in any language, in which a word is placed when
   the person is addressed: as Domine, O Lord.
